Mozambique Plans $380 Million Upgrade of Maputo Port, Noticias Reports

-- B y   F r e d   K a t e r e r e
-- 
2011-07-23T07:17:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-23/mozambique-plans-380-million-upgrade-of-maputo-port-noticias-reports.html
Mozambique plans to invest $380
million to double capacity at the port in the capital, Maputo,
to 40 million metric tons, Noticias reported, citing Camilo
Abdul, a representative of the port.  Botswana intends to ship 20 million tons of coal and other
minerals through the port, the Maputo-based newspaper reported,
citing Rosario Mualeia, the chairman of the state-controlled
ports and railways utility, Caminhos de Ferro de Mocambique.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Fred Katerere in Maputo at 
 fkaterere@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Ana Monteiro at 
 amonteiro4@bloomberg.net  